Drafting Date: {{ drafting_date }}

AGREEMENT

THIS AGREEMENT is made at {{ location }} on this {{ date }}

BETWEEN: {{ party_a_name }}, residing at {{ party_a_address }}, hereinafter called 'The First Party'.

AND: {{ party_b_name }}, residing at {{ party_b_address }}, hereinafter called 'The Second Party'.

WHEREAS:
1. The First Party is {{ party_a_status }}.
2. The Second Party has agreed to {{ agreement_purpose }}.

TERMS AND CONDITIONS:
- {{ condition_1 }}
- {{ condition_2 }}

(Note: Standard general agreement format following the Indian Contract Act, 1872.)

Drafting Date: {{ drafting_date }}

LEGAL NOTICE

To,
{{ recipient_name }}
{{ recipient_address }}

Subject: {{ notice_subject }}

Dear Sir/Madam,

Under instructions from my client, {{ client_name }}, residing at {{ client_address }}, I hereby serve you with the following legal notice:

1. My client is the owner/aggrieved party in the matter of {{ matter_summary }}.
2. FACTUAL BACKGROUND: {{ factual_details }}
3. GRIEVANCE: That you have failed to {{ breach_description }}.
4. DEMAND: You are hereby called upon to {{ demand_action }} within {{ notice_period }} days from the receipt of this notice.
5. CAUSE OF ACTION: Failing which, my client has given me clear instructions to initiate civil/criminal proceedings against you at your cost and consequences.

Yours faithfully,

{{ lawyer_name }}
Advocate, {{ city }}

(Note: Derived from LexForti and iPleaders standard Indian legal notice modules.)
